      <h3 style="color:#fc8f39;">GENTLE GIANT'S GALLOPING GENERATIONS</h3>
      <p>Moving on with the generations is not the only reason of our existence. We at <b>Navnath Group</b> count every single moment of our work to fulfill dreams of countless happiness of the lives. Ever since its inception in 1910, Navnath group is reoriented during its journey with the emerging global culture and lifestyles.</p>
      <p>The foundation of today's successful business laid in 1910 by <b>Late Shri Chintaman Joshi.</b> A first drop of sweat went into the establishment of a new transport company named as Chintaman Parshuram & Co. The company was experiencing expansion in the same transportation business when <b>Mr. Ballal Joshi,</b> son of Late Shri Chintaman Joshi took responsibilities on his strong young shoulders. A son who was lessoned ethical and transparent business skills under the wings of his father slowly enhanced the capabilities under a new banner of M. K. J. & Company.</p>
      <p>In 1975, the company witnessed the most influential paradigm shift in its business when Mr. Ballal Joshi diversified into construction activity by establishing a new firm named as Shree Chintamani Builders. Every step in this business had steadily focused on creating a better experience in every aspect of life. The success story which already spanned across decades continues to achieve higher targets relentlessly, for excellence in architecture and quality constructions.</p>
      <p>The business had progressively expanded its footprint in various parts of Mumbai and other regions. In 2007, we aligned this business to better leverage the strengths of its existing projects and the synergies from the new developments. Our singular goal is to provide ONE structure, ONE offering and ONE face to our people. Under a spiritual influence Navnath Group was evolved with a legacy of supreme principles - honesty, selflessness, austerity and devotion of nine super-super human beings.</p>
      <p>While rooting deep into believes of the people, <b>Mr. Vaibhav Joshi</b>, son of Mr. Ballal Joshi stepped in 1980 and eventually became a partner in Prasad Constructions in 1985. A man who blessed with a heritage of values and culture from his forefathers envisions every project and each minute detail in it. In 1995 and 2001, Mr. Vaibhav Joshi set up his own proprietary concerns with Neelam Constructions and Mukul Constructions.</p>
      <p>Today <b>Mr. Shardool Joshi</b>, son of Mr. Vaibhav Joshi is working on residential and commercial projects along with his father. The higher standards set by the duo in its pursuit to transform into a group to reckon with. In order to achieve the scalability required to undertake large developments, we never compromise on outsourcing work. Our own engineers, equipments, machineries and engendered experienced labour make us 'Special ONE'.</p>
